external_knowledge:
- 'folks' refers to individuals in the database;
- 'job roles' correspond to the 'workclass' column;
- 'marital statuses' refer to the 'marital_status' column;
- 'personal details' includes age, workclass, education, occupation, relationship, race, sex, capital gain, capital loss, hours per week, country, and income.

- "sailed to the shores of prosperity" refers to individuals with an income greater than 50,000;
- "families that form a mini-community of five or more" indicates households with a size of 5 or more individuals;
- "residents of the land of the free and home of the brave" denotes individuals living in the United States;
- "crossed the educational bridge of high school" means individuals with an education number of at least 12, which typically signifies a high school education or higher.

sql:
SELECT age, workclass
FROM individuals
WHERE age > 30 AND workclass = 'Private';

SELECT individual_id, age, income
FROM individuals
WHERE age > 50 AND income = '>50K';

external_knowledge:
- 'nests' metaphorically refers to 'households';
- 'more than a solitary feather' means 'households with more than one individual';
- 'birds' signify 'individuals';
- 'cumulative age of these feathered friends' relates to the sum of ages of individuals within the household.

sql:
SELECT individuals.individual_id, incomes.income
FROM individuals
JOIN incomes ON individuals.income = incomes.income_id;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM individuals
WHERE occupation = 'Exec-managerial' AND workclass = 'Private';

external_knowledge:
- "planted their roots firmly in the soil of adulthood" refers to individuals aged 20 or older;
- "bearing the golden fruits of wealth" is a metaphorical way to describe individuals with a capital gain greater than 70,000;
- "tasted the nectar of prosperity" symbolizes individuals with an income level above 50,000.

sql:
SELECT AVG(age) AS average_age
FROM individuals
WHERE age > 50 AND income = '>50K';

SELECT AVG(age) AS avg_age
FROM individuals
WHERE capital_gain > 0 AND income = '>50K';

external_knowledge:
- High-earners are those with an income level of '>50K';
- Self-employed refers to individuals with a 'Self-emp-not-inc' workclass;
- Employment history is listed from the most recent to the oldest start date;
- Income history is listed from the most recent to the oldest year.
